commit 1f36bde8713087f420835b0eb55a6a098baf9b1a
Author: Jiri Konecny <jkonecny@redhat.com>
Date:   Mon Jun 8 18:56:09 2020 +0200

    Change license in spec file to LGPLv3+

commit 85b2a45c4c01baf13c6a334aef7c729b64d68053
Author: Jiri Konecny <jkonecny@redhat.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 9 12:00:49 2020 +0200

    Add COPR badge for daily builds

commit 2fd75ad6eec9e0b01ec600f5ce954bedbae81238
Author: Jiri Konecny <jkonecny@redhat.com>
Date:   Mon Jun 8 18:55:33 2020 +0200

    Improve setup.py
    
    Add missing information.

commit 4fa0f1182217aa0c1a0c481acb8c047bf28167d4
Author: Jiri Konecny <jkonecny@redhat.com>
Date:   Mon Jun 8 18:35:42 2020 +0200

    Change license to LGPLv3 for all the files

commit a8d63b9e8eb2eacbafb113a7983e7e8e6aeb7af1
Author: Jiri Konecny <jkonecny@redhat.com>
Date:   Mon Jun 8 15:36:33 2020 +0200

    Change License from GPLv2+ to LGPLv3+
    
    This library will have much better benefit from LGPL than GPL. GPL
    license were inherited from Anaconda project where this project
    were originated from. However, Anaconda is end user program but
    Simpleline is general Text UI library. Such a library should be
    available for anyone so LGPL is much better suited.
    
    The original code from Anaconda was contributed only by Anaconda team
    members and all of them are/were Red Hat employees. All the new code in
    simpleline is also contributed only by Anaconda team members who are
    Red Hat employees. In that case re-licensing is not a problem here.

commit 3973611d8a2704be7d08b9b1db732aa8e14766fb
Author: Jiri Konecny <jkonecny@redhat.com>
Date:   Thu Aug 22 11:49:30 2019 +0200

    New version - 1.6

commit fcaa82ac1a40d90d9166616f21a4edeea19fa306
Merge: b61121f b24fd67
Author: Jiri Konecny <jkonecny@redhat.com>
Date:   Thu Aug 1 09:30:39 2019 +0200

    Merge pull request #60 from poncovka/master-password_dialog
    
    Always close the password dialog

commit b24fd679ae7aefb7d845b1ed1418fba603894f5c
Author: Vendula Poncova <vponcova@redhat.com>
Date:   Mon Jul 29 18:28:18 2019 +0200

    Always close the password dialog
    
    The password dialog should be closed even if no password is provided.
    Otherwise, it is not possible to continue, because the UI is blocked.

commit b61121f3707826ebe0e025ea4dd81e07e4ddc2fd
