    New version - 1.4

commit 6dfe482aaddcb57a5a7a2597a96b1ff913c51f70
Merge: c4e7e38 8c64112
Author: Jiri Konecny <jkonecny@redhat.com>
Date:   Mon Nov 19 16:27:59 2018 +0100

    Merge pull request #59 from jkonecny12/master_add_test_to_run_app_with_empty_stack
    
    Kill the run call with an empty screen stack

commit 8c641122a7b362d8ba6100d99ae40e6ddcfe7c3b
Author: Jiri Konecny <jkonecny@redhat.com>
Date:   Mon Nov 19 13:15:15 2018 +0100

    Fix and add tests for the new changes (#1646568)

commit e1c6d2c97331276312179467182eeee072753f3a
Author: Jiri Konecny <jkonecny@redhat.com>
Date:   Mon Nov 19 13:09:42 2018 +0100

    Add should_run_with_empty_stack configuration (#1646568)
    
    This configuration will be by default False. It will kill the
    application instead of staying in an infinite loop with no user
    information.
    
    The infinite loop is sometimes required behavior. In that case a
    developer can just set configuration to True so it will behave as
    before.

commit f669c7cdb4b78df3852f4b980fc049f5663ffb17
Author: Jiri Konecny <jkonecny@redhat.com>
Date:   Mon Nov 19 13:07:59 2018 +0100

    Remove wrong line in password_function conf

