commit 4d270325d784582fdbcd580e07c1cf581c952ecd
Merge: 2045611 8f5791a
Author: Jiri Konecny <jkonecny@redhat.com>
Date:   Thu Jun 7 11:52:55 2018 +0200

    Merge pull request #57 from jkonecny12/master-fix-pylint
    
    Fix pylint errors raised by new pylint version

commit 8f5791a0ea9b314cfe20f1695e2fa7a8e1a321a1
Author: Jiri Konecny <jkonecny@redhat.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 5 16:47:57 2018 +0200

    Fix pylint errors raised by new pylint version
    
    Most solved by pylint disable but there is one improvement.

commit 60822c9b82ac05e2257a7867d68215d473d7e58e
Author: Jiri Konecny <jkonecny@redhat.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 5 13:00:29 2018 +0200

    Setup logging handler properly for a library
    
    The logging settings can't be changed once it is configured. This is
    especially bad in case of library. Use NullHandler which is recommended
    by Python 3 documentation.
    
    https://docs.python.org/3/howto/logging.html#library-config

commit 2045611190d025f6d98e3bdec8b350e8bcfc9a90
Author: Jiri Konecny <jkonecny@redhat.com>
